# Privacy Policy


ARplugz (hereinafter referred to as the “Developer”) hereby establishes this Privacy Policy (hereinafter referred to as this “Policy”) regarding the handling of user information in connection with the Android application “[App Name]” (hereinafter referred to as the “App”) provided by the Developer.

## Article 1. Scope of Application

This Policy applies to the collection, use, storage, disclosure, and other handling of user information in connection with the use of the App.

## Article 2. Information Collected

The App does not contain any functionality through which the Developer directly collects personal information that can directly identify a user, including the user’s name, address, telephone number, or email address.

However, the App uses third-party advertising services for purposes including advertising delivery, measurement of advertising effectiveness, prevention of fraudulent activity, improvement of the quality of the App, and other related purposes.

In connection with the use of such services, the following information may be collected automatically:

1. Advertising identifiers
2. IP addresses
3. Device information, including device type, operating system, and language settings
4. Information regarding the use of the App, user interactions, and advertisement impressions and clicks
5. Crash information, diagnostic information, and performance information
6. Approximate location information
7. Other information required by advertising service providers for the provision of their services

Such information is not ordinarily collected for the purpose of enabling the Developer to directly identify individual users.

## Article 3. Advertising Services

The App uses Google AdMob, an advertising service provided by Google LLC.

Google AdMob may collect advertising identifiers, device information, IP addresses, usage information, and other information necessary to display advertisements based on user interests and usage, measure advertising effectiveness, prevent fraudulent activity, and provide advertising services.

For further information regarding Google’s handling of information, please refer to Google’s privacy policy and other applicable terms and policies.

